column4: I am ready... my log file is at: http://paste.ubuntu.com/187166/
this log messages identify that my bios is corrupt.. starting with that... i have more issues
Also, i need to know if loading all that bluetooth stuff is ok or normal, because i think that's how i am being hacked
I mean, I have no bluetooth devices installed on my system, yet it loads that stuff....
you're just paranoid
How do you know?
I mean, you 're saying my log is normal?
I don't see too much unusual about that dmesg output
the BIOS may be corrupt message appears to have been written by a non-native English speaker
or could just be cryptic. probably anticipating buggy phoenix bios, but not necessarily a problem
also, are you sure your system has no bluetooth capability? if not, the kernel built for the desktop might be anticipating future usage, or something like that.
looks ok to me assuming you are on supposed to be on the 10 network and your DNS server is in fact 10.3.1.125
My mother board is an ASUS model M2NPV-VM, and it does'nt have any mother board bluetooth , and i have no peripherials but a grub hard disk
no worries. i dont have bluetooth and I see the same messages.
Are you sure?
I'm positive about the bluetooth
http://pastebin.com/f74a5d9ff
I mean, is it normal to have an pan0 interface loaded after booting?
yes
none taken
say what?
It ain't an accusation....
okay, I'm going to be going away in a few seconds. but based on what I saw from the pastebin, you look fine to me. good luck.
